esearchers compiled a social inventory of Morocco that in turn led to the emergence of a new object of study, Moroccan Islam, and a new field, Moroccan studies. In the process, they resurrected the monarchy and reinvented Morocco as a modern polity. This is an important contribution for scholars and readers interested in questions of orientalism and empire, colonialism and modernity, and the invention of traditions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFrenchzMoroccoxIntellectual life. 0aIslam and statezMoroccoxHistoryy20th century. 0aIslamzMorocco. 70(DE-601)1062834990(DE-588)4027743-4aIslam2gnd 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh  aafrican history.  abritish colonialism.  abritish imperialism.  acolonial officers.  acolonial policies.  acolonialism.  aearly 20th century history.  aempire.  aeuropean colonialism.  afrench colonialism.  afrench ethnographers.  afrench imperialism.  aindia.  ainvention of traditions.  aislam.  amission scientifique du maroc.  amodern polity.  amodernity.  amonarchy.  amoroccan islam.  amoroccan studies.  amorocco.  amuslim countries.  amuslim.  anational form of islam.  anorth african history.  aorientalism.  apolitical.  areligion.  areligious studies.  astate formation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052027381840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095799240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520957992423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520957992/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY